text:
Came here on MLK weekend and Jeremih performed at the day pool. It technically wasn't really pool season but there was a huge tent covering and I guess a heating system to give that impression of summer, even though it was pretty cloudy. The water was pretty lukewarm, which was fine but didn't help too much since it was winter lol. They were playing the playoff game between Packers and Seahawks while the Dj was playing some music so I was glad I got to dance and swim while witnessing my hawks win. Obviously they stopped the game while Jeremih performed and I was just hearing from word of mouth of what happened in the game. Lots of beach balls flying around and I decided to keep one of them (;

We got pulled into a booth. Very cute and sleek looking white couch for my friends and I to dance on. There were liquors and chasers provided as well. We got this huge fishbowl drink (okay probably wouldn't call it a fishbowl, but it was huge) that my 12 friends and I shared. It was around $150 and it got us pretty drunk. Very delicious though!

Overall a very fun place that plays good music! I would come here again if the occasion calls for it. I would try to come here for the night club as well when I get the chance!
